Pour the @Water for the Rice{300%milliliter} into a #medium saucepan{} with a 
tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and @salt{1/4%tsp} 
and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover 
with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still 
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to 
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @Carrot{1}(trimmed and peeled). Use the #peeler{} 
to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Rice Vinegar{15%milliliter}, @Sugar for the 
Pickle{1/2%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Add the 
carrot ribbons, toss to coat, then set aside to pickle.

Halve the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%grams} widthways. Peel and grate the @Garlic 
Clove{1}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once 
hot, add the Tenderstem® and stir-fry for ~{2-3%mins}.

Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}, then add a splash of 
water. Cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) and allow to cook until tender, 
~{4-6%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

In a medium bowl, combine the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, 
@Plain Flour{1%tbsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%grams} and toss to coat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat. 
Once hot, fry the chicken until golden and crispy, ~{8-10%mins}. Turn 
frequently to ensure it doesn't burn.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's 
> no pink in the middle.

When the chicken is crispy, pour in the @Bulgogi Sauce{150%grams}, 
@Sambal Paste{15%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), half the 
@Soy Sauce{15%milliliter} and the @Water for the Sauce{50%milliliter}. Stir to 
combine, bring to the boil and simmer until thickened slightly, 
~{1-2%mins}. Remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the 
remaining @Soy Sauce{}.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}. Top with the bulgogi chicken, garlic 
broccoli and pickled carrot in separate sections. Enjoy!